history.text: Did you know that La La Land was filmed in Cinemascope?
Interesting, no I did not know that. Did you know that La La Land stars Emma Stone? I like her.
I like her too - Ryan Gosling was a good actor in this as well.
Yes, he sure was. There was a lot of showbiz and dancing, which was entertaining.
The movie got a little slow in the middle, but it picked up in the end
I definitely agree, it seems a lot of people also agree that the two leads weren't that great at dancing, so maybe they thought it was a bit slow.
The music scene in Los Angeles was interesting to see in the movie however
Definitely, I also liked that it's a fantasy and kind of like being in a place we might dream of.
It was definitely a fantasy like the old style of Hollywood musicals.
For sure. It was directed by Damien Chazelle. I'm not sure if I've seen any of his other movies.
I can understand why Sebastian would not want to play Christmas songs.  That would get old quickly.
Haha, for sure. It seems his jazz improvisation really peeked the interest of Mia.
I can understand it.   She definitely was trying to tease him by requesting a song that he hated as well.
Absolutely, I'm glad he went along with her and they connect and chat in the car.
It is a classic love story in the musical part of LA
Yeah, and they threw in some 1980's music, which was fun.
80's music is always fun even if it is not the jazz that Sebastian loves
Yeah, he really loves it. I really liked the part where Sebastian suggests that Mia write a one woman show.
Yes it was great that she wrote a play, but it was sad that Sebastian ended up playing in a band that he did not enjoy.
Yeah, it is sad that he didn't enjoy it. But it did give him steady income, which helped financially after Mia and he moved in together.
RIght.  It was sad that he just did it because he knew Mia was getting pressure from her mother.  Mother-in-laws ya know?
Haha, absolutely. And it made Mia upset to see him sad, so that's no good.
I know.  But not following his dream was ultimately what led to their breakup
Yeah, that was sad. Mia said she liked him more when he was unsuccessful, but following his dreams.
But she followed her dream and had a horribly unsuccessful play.
She did, and Sebastian misses the play. That was hard to watch.
It was very sad  and I hated the fact that she was unable to forgive him
I know, me too. I wish she would have forgiven him. I can't believe she had to move back to Nevada.
I know - and going back to her Nevada and giving up on her dreams?  That was sad.
Yeah, leaving her dreams and her love, kinda depressing.
It was depressing.  But Nevada might be a less stressful place to live than LA
